  "text": "Humans are able to recognize materials, compare their appearance, or even infer many of their key properties e ortlessly, just by brie y looking at them. Many works propose classi cation techniques, although it seems clear that labels do not su ce to capture the richness of our subjective experience with real-world materials ]. Unfortunately, the underlying perceptual process of material recognition is complex, involving many distinct variables; such process is not yet completely understood [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
